## Customer Roles and Configurations  

#### Who is a "Customer"?  
The term "Customer" refers to the organization or individual setting up the Services. For accounts registered using a corporate email domain, the associated organization will be considered the Customer. The Customer retains rights to manage configurations, roles, and permissions for the Services.  

#### Who is an "Authorized User"?  
An "Authorized User" is an individual (employee, contractor, or client) invited to use the Services. Depending on the subscription, Authorized Users may have varying levels of access—ranging from building workflows and applications ("Custom Apps") to accessing these apps as end users.  

#### Building and Using Custom Apps  
Custom Apps can be created by arranging DronaHQ's components (e.g., tables, charts, forms) via a user-friendly interface. These apps integrate with various databases or data resources ("Databases"), allowing Authorized Users to execute queries, workflows, or business logic seamlessly.  

#### What Constitutes "Customer Data"?  
"Customer Data" includes any information submitted by Authorized Users within Custom Apps. The Customer maintains control over this data, including permissions, retention, and access settings. DronaHQ processes Customer Data strictly per Customer instructions. Customers are responsible for informing Authorized Users of relevant policies and ensuring compliance with applicable data protection laws.  

