## Payment obligation

#### Service Fees  
For annual subscription plans and specific pre-approved monthly plans (collectively, “Prepaid Plans”), service fees must be paid in advance before the subscription begins, including any renewals. Fees for these plans are detailed on the Subscription Page, based on the number of Authorized Users specified at the time of purchase.

For monthly subscription plans not classified as Prepaid Plans, fees are determined by:

1. The Customer’s actual usage during the monthly billing period.
2. Our current rates for Authorized Users, as outlined in the pricing details.

At the end of each monthly billing cycle, an invoice will be generated, and payment will be due immediately.

Payment obligations for Services are non-cancellable, and except as explicitly stated in the Contract, fees are non-refundable. All payments must be made using a valid credit card. By submitting payment details, the Customer authorizes us and relevant financial institutions to process charges for all applicable fees, including renewals and any usage overages.

#### Subscription Overages  
If the Customer exceeds usage limits specified in their plan, including the number of Authorized Users or other metrics detailed on the Subscription Page, the Customer agrees to pay the additional fees for the excess use.

#### Expert Services  
Fees for Expert Services, if applicable, are outlined in the Order Form. Unless otherwise stated, payment for Expert Services must be made in full within 30 days of the invoice date. These fees are non-cancellable and non-refundable, except as expressly stated in the Contract.

#### Taxes  
All fees are exclusive of taxes, duties, or similar charges. The Customer is responsible for paying any applicable taxes, except for taxes based on our net income. If withholding taxes are required by law, the Customer agrees to reimburse us for such amounts.

#### Late Payments  
If payment is not received by the due date, we reserve the right to take the following actions:

1. Suspend or terminate access to the Services and/or Expert Services after notifying the Customer (via email or other means).
2. Downgrade the subscription plan to a free tier upon notice to the Customer.

#### Credits  
Credits applied to the Customer’s account (e.g., promotional offers) will expire upon the termination of the Contract. These credits hold no cash value and are neither transferable nor refundable.

